EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO AUTHORIZING THE AMENDMENT OF THE WARWICK CITY CHARTER
TO ALLOW FOR ELECTRONIC NOTICE OF SPECIAL COUNCIL MEETINGS, RAISING
THE SMALL PROCUREMENT DOLLAR THRESHOLD BY ORDINANCE, AND
ESTABLISHING MINORITY REPRESENTATION APPOINTMENTS TO BOARDS AND
COMMISSIONS VIA ORDINANCE
***
1 This act would approve charter amendments to the Warwick city charter subject to voter
2 approval at the general election to be held in November, 2026, or at a special election as may be
3 scheduled sooner. If approved, these amendments would allow the methods of notifying city
4 council members of special meetings to be expanded to include electronic notification, would allow
5 the monetary thresholds for competitive bids of small purchases to be adjustable by ordinance as
6 allowed by the state, and would further provide that the city council could establish via ordinance
7 standards for minority representation appointments to city boards and commissions.
8 Sections 1, 2, and 3 of this act would take effect if a majority of those electors qualified to
9 vote upon the corresponding question in Section 4 shall vote in favor thereof. The remaining
10 sections of this act would take effect upon passage.
